  "observations": [
    "Pipeline kanban — startup screen, not a tab; columns = stages, cards = deals with title + amount + days-in-stage + activity icons",
    "Drag-drop between stage columns is the primary mechanism for advancing deals (replace deal.stage)",
    "Color-coded rot indicator on every card: green/yellow/red/purple derived from nextActivityAt + lastActivityAt + stage.rottenDays",
    "Activity-based selling = coercive constraint: a deal without scheduled next-activity is rendered red — UI invariant pushing 'always have a next step'",
    "Stage column footers show aggregate row: total amount, weighted (probability-adjusted) amount, deal count",
    "Multiple pipelines (New Business / Renewals / Service) — pipeline is a scoping selector at the top of the kanban",
    "Leads Inbox is a separate surface from pipeline — pre-qualified records held back so the deal kanban stays clean",
    "Convert Lead → Deal is a dedicated transition action that carries person + organization links forward",
    "Deal detail is hero (title/amount/stage/close-date/owner) + tabbed sidebar (Notes/Activities/Email/Files/Calls/Documents/Products)",
    "'Schedule next activity' is a persistent CTA on every deal — one-click typed activity creation (Call/Meeting/Email/Task/Lunch/Custom)",
    "Activities timeline is a centralized cross-deal list, filterable by user/type/status, with calendar two-way sync overlay",
    "Smart Bcc — emailing a magic address auto-creates EmailMessage linked by recipient match (auto-link via email pattern)",
    "Email tracking surfaces opens + link clicks as inline metadata on EmailMessage rows",
    "Insights = configurable dashboard: forecast, stage-to-stage funnel conversion, deal duration, activity counts per rep",
    "Goals are visible everywhere with real-time progress bars — scope = personal/team/company",
    "Workflow Automation = trigger (deal.stage changed / deal.status=won) → action template (schedule activity, create project, send email)",
    "AI Sales Assistant surfaces recommendations as inline cards: 'Deal X has no activity for 7 days — schedule one' (one-click accept)",
    "Smart Docs generated from templates merge deal fields → PDF + embedded e-signature with view-tracking shareable links",
    "Projects appear as a post-sale handoff: 'Create project from won deal' is the primary lifecycle bridge",
    "Visibility groups gate deal access at row level: own / team / everyone — admin-configurable permission sets",
    "Mobile pipeline view = swipeable stage columns; quick-log activities and voice notes attach to deals",
    "Caller-ID integration recognizes incoming calls against Person.phones and offers quick-log Activity",
    "LeadFinder / Smart Contact Data enriches Person and Organization from public sources — enrichment is a replace on enrichedFrom",
    "Dashboard answers 'what to do next', not 'what happened' — Activities Inbox (overdue / today) is the morning surface for sales reps"
  ]
}